Master Baker - "If a Wiz can't bake how can he nuke?"<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uvokalkhords.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vokal Khords</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(12/12/01 10:22:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards...........screw you And VI to</span><hr size=1> It would seem the problem could be solved by nerfing PB AoEs. I'm not calling for another class to be nerfed but do mages/wizards ever use these in a non-AE group? Chanters and bards use them when the feces hit the spinning blades but those are defensive in nature.<br>
