Master Baker - "If a Wiz can't bake how can he nuke?"<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhiraghm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hiraghm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kindly Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(12/12/01 11:20:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xtimports.com/data/graphics/Aldrinshroom1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards...........screw you And VI to</span><hr size=1> I've talked about difficulties I have getting a group in here before... and what the other wizards are saying I've also noticed. For a change, I'm invited to groups; people wait for me to get set up or get there. They reserve a slot for me. This is in Fungus Grove. I got in a group the other night, and there were two wizzies, a cleric, a chanter, a mage and a shaman. We pulled between 5 and 10 mobs, and the lvl 60 wiz and I would chain our big AEs while the chanter kept the mobs mezzed. True, we didn't need tanks. But there are lots and lots and lots of zones and spawns that need tanks but don't need wizzies. Even more that need clerics or chanters but don't need wizzies. Yes, wizzies, like druids, can quad kite; no sane wizard will quad kite with a pb AE spell. Mages can solo with their pets, necros can solo with their pets, I once saw an enchanter soloing 4 spectres in Oasis (ages ago.) So why do people piss and moan about wizards/druids being able to quad-kite solo? I have a heckuva time just soloing ice giants, and each 1 I kill means I have to sit and regenerate almost a full bar of mana. Unless there's a resist, in which case I get to CR. I haven't had the gonads to try quad kiting yet, because I know that is exceptionally dangerous. <br>
Night before last I was in a group hunting Tarmoks in Fungal Grove. They're supposed to be non-aggro, but we kept getting extras. I overnuked one, knowing I could root it and run out of range and let the ranger pound it the rest of the way dead. Except you can't root, you can't snare the sobs. Later, we had two wizards, a mage, two rangers, and one other non-pure-caster, and we wizards couldn't fart in the mobs direction without it going nuts on us. I'd just hit it with temperate flux, and unless I was half a zone away, it'd come for me. And we're not supposed to use AE and mez on these critters??<br>
Why the heck is verant so darned afraid of wizards? We're all offense and no defense, not even warriors are all defense and no offense. There's not another class that's all offense and no defense to our degree, not even rangers. <br>
Here's some of the changes Verant has made to my disappointment:<br>
Made my bard look like an idiot<br>
Taken away my dwarve's summersault (so I've been told)<br>
Made my iksar monk look like a frog<br>
Taken away the funny FD animation that made me create an ikky monk<br>
made my ranger look like an idiot, no matter what armor I put on him.<br>
made the rather cool looking &quot;floating turd&quot; Earth elemental look like an oversized mudman<br>
given me a useless pet that *might* regenerate mana faster, but will for darned sure eat mana when I zone or invis (guaranteed to lose familiar when I zone into/outof Dawnshadow. lost two and a half bubbles of health once)<br>
(the invis might be a bug; if so, fix it)<br>
Made the super uber eternal robe look like gossimer and require a tough group with a lot of luck to get.<br>
Made the 4 existing Propylons self-only. While it might be unfair for the 4 of us to be popular or make money by porting groups up to Luclin, it sure would make life a lot easier for people, especially those on CR, to not have to wait for the stupid spires.<br>
But none of these affected fighting. <br>
The pbAE groups were *fun* and *different* for a change. No more &quot;root nuke med&quot; or &quot;med til half health, nuke once, stand and wait for mob to aggro melee, med, wait for next mob&quot;. <br>
I love gravity flux. I don't get to use it much because everyone is terrified of it (even those who laugh when I boing the mobs.)<br>
Btw, you can't use thunderclap effectively to do pbAE. Why? it has a knockback effect. If you give superdupernova and the next higher pbAE a knockback effect, it will be used less or at least on a fewer number of mobs at once. Why? Same reason grav flux isn't used; it knocks the mobs about, spreads them out so AE is less effective. And the knockback effect would make it more effective in a defensive situation (yes, I've used thunderclap to knock a mob away from a melee who was getting lunched because he and the mob were both rooted. )<br>
But no. Nerf the zone instead.<br>
